    "created_at": "2024-12-16T16:04:43Z",
    "updated_at": "2024-12-16T16:33:25Z",
    "body": "I have this too, but:\r\n\r\n- It doesn't happen when I am using zsh directly on my macbook with iTerm2\r\n- It does happen when I am logged into my linux machine via SSH (still iTerm2, also \r\n- After using a multiline command the starting position of the cursor has moved 2 characters to the right, whatever was in the first 2 characters will stay visible\r\n\r\nLocale variables seem to be set:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n❯ env | grep LC_\r\nLC_TERMINAL=iTerm2\r\nLC_TERMINAL_VERSION=3.5.5\r\nLC_CTYPE=en_US.UTF-8\r\nLC_ALL=en_US.UTF-8\r\n```\r\n\r\nEdit: This also might be relevant\r\n It also happens in Terminal.app and the VSCode builtin terminal for me, and it stops happening when I set `export PS1=\"> \"`.\r\nThe closest stackoverflow question I can find says something about not needing `%{...%}` in certain cases, maybe that is part of the issue?: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/39423333/zsh-bug-on-multiline-commands-deleting-messes-up-characters\r\n\r\nIn case it helps here us the raw output of my PS1:\r\n\r\nOn the server:\r\n```\r\n\r\n%{\u001b[1;2;32m%}🌐my_server %{\u001b[0m%}%{\u001b[38;2;218;98;125m%}%{\u001b[0m%}%{\u001b[48;2;218;98;125m%} ~ %{\u001b[48;2;252;161;125;38;2;218;98;125m%}%{\u001b[48;2;134;187;216;38;2;252;161;125m%}%{\u001b[48;2;6;150;154;38;2;134;187;216m%}%{\u001b[0m%}%{\u001b[38;2;6;150;154m%}%{\u001b[0m%}\r\n%{\u001b[1;32m%}❯%{\u001b[0m%} \r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nOn the macbook:\r\n```\r\n\r\n%{\u001b[38;2;218;98;125m%}%{\u001b[0m%}%{\u001b[48;2;218;98;125m%} ~ %{\u001b[48;2;252;161;125;38;2;218;98;125m%}%{\u001b[48;2;134;187;216;38;2;252;161;125m%}%{\u001b[48;2;6;150;154;38;2;134;187;216m%}%{\u001b[0m%}%{\u001b[38;2;6;150;154m%}%{\u001b[0m%}\r\n%{\u001b[1;32m%}❯%{\u001b[0m%} \r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nEdit 2:\r\nAs the main difference between the prompt seemed to be the hostname part, I removed that and it still happened. I also tried it without a newline in the prompt and noticed that it adds approximately the same amount of characters to the \"stuck\" part as the length of the prompt:\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/577ad8a9-7c2e-45ac-9bf9-b3f863b4abe9)\r\n",
